 Big Horn and Yellowstone expedition of 1876, and in the campaign on the British border, in 1879 |publisher=Donohue Brothers }}\n* {{Cite journal|last=Kraft |first=Louis |authorlink= |year=2008 |title=Custer: The Truth Behind the Silver Screen Myth |journal=American History |volume= |issue=Feb |pages=26\u201333  |url=}}\n* {{Cite book |last=Newsom |first=T.M. |year=2007|url=http://digicoll.library.wisc.edu/cgi-bin/History/History-idx?id=History.Newson |title=Thrilling scenes among the Indians. With a graphic description of Custer's last fight with Sitting Bull |publisher=Kessinger Publishing, LLC |accessdate=2012-07-17\n|isbn=978-0-548-62988-8}}\n* Stiles, T.J. ''Custer's Trials: A Life on the Frontier of a New America'' (2015), Pulitzer Prize. \n* {{Cite book |last=Victor |first=F.F. |authorlink=Frances Fuller Victor|year=1877 |title=Eleven years in the Rocky Mountains and life on the frontier also a history of the Sioux war, and a life Gen. George A. Custer, with a full account of his last battle |publisher=Columbian book company |title-link=wikisource:en:A History of the Sioux War, and a Life of Gen. George A. Custer, with a Full Account of his Last Battle }}\n* {{Cite book |last=Whittaker |first=F. |year=1876|url=http://digital.library.wisc.edu/1711.dl/History.Whittaker\n|title=A complete life of Gen. George A. Custer : Major-General of Volunteers; Brevet Major-General, U.S. Army; and Lieutenant-Colonel, Seventh U.S. Cavalry |publisher=Sheldon and Company }} {{ISBN|978-0-9966994-3-3}}\n* {{Cite book |last=Donovan |first=J. |year=2009|url=https://archive.org/details/isbn_9780316155786 |url-access=registration |quote=A Terrible Glory: Custer and the Little Bighorn. |title=A Terrible Glory: Custer and the Little Bighorn \u2013 The Last Great Battle of the American West |publisher= Little, Brown & Company |isbn= 978-0-316-06747-8}}\n\n==External links==\n{{Commons|George Armstrong Custer}}\n* [http://worldhistory.us/military-history/indian-wars-and-the-year-of-george-custer-finding-the-indians.php Indian Wars and the Year of George Custer]\n* [http://www.friendslittlebighorn.com Friends of the Little Bighorn Battlefield]\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/*/http://www.kshs.org/portraits/custer_elizabeth.htm Custer Battlefield Museum]\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20120406011637/http://www.thelbha.org/home.shtml Little Big Horn Associates]\n* [http://www.littlebighorn.info Little Bighorn History Alliance]\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20130514172105/http://library.uww.edu/special-collections/special-collections/hammer-collection Kenneth M Hammer Collection on Custer and the Battle of the Little Bighorn, Harold G. Andersen Library, University of Wisconsin-Whitewater]\n* [[commons:Custer|Gallery of Custer images]]\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20100731202833/http://digital.library.okstate.edu/encyclopedia/entries/C/CU011.html Encyclopedia of Oklahoma History and Culture -Custer, George Armstrong]\n* {{Cite EB1911|wstitle=Custer, George Armstrong |short=x}}\n* {{Cite Appletons' |last=Custer |first=Elizabeth Bacon |authorlink=Elizabeth Bacon Custer |wstitle=Custer, George Armstrong|year=1900 |notaref=x |short=x}}\n* {{librivox author|id=2109|title=Gen. George A. Custer}}\n* [https://findingaid.lib.byu.edu/viewItem/Vault%20MSS%20364/ George A. and Elizabeth B. Custer papers, Vault MSS 364] at [[L. Tom Perry Special Collections]], [[Harold B. Lee Library]], [[Brigham Young University]]\n\n{{American frontier}}\n{{Gettysburg figures|state=collapsed}}\n{{Black Hills, South Dakota}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Custer, George Armstrong}}\n[[Category:1839 births]]\n[[Category:1876 deaths]]\n[[Category:George Armstrong Custer| ]]\n[[Category:People from Harrison County, Ohio]]\n[[Category:American people of German descent]]\n[[Category:United States Army generals]]\n[[Category:Union Army generals]]\n[[Category:People of Ohio in the American Civil War]]\n[[Category:People of Michigan in the American Civil War]]\n[[Category: