{"title_page": "Jos\u00e9 Carrasco (politician)", "text_new": "{{for|the Spanish footballer|Francisco Jos\u00e9 Carrasco}}\n{{for|the Colombian long-distance runner|Jos\u00e9 Alirio Carrasco}}\n[[File:Jos\u00e9 Carrasco 2.jpg|thumb|Jos\u00e9 Carrasco]]\n'''Jos\u00e9 Carlos Carrasco T\u00e1vara''' (1944 \u2013 18 January 2015) was a [[Peru]]vian politician and a [[Congress of Peru|Congressman]] representing [[Piura Region|Piura]] for the 2006\u20132011 term. Carrasco belonged to the [[Peruvian Aprista Party]]. He was born in Sullana.\n\nHe died in Lima on 18 January 2015 from lung cancer, aged 70.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.larepublica.pe/16-01-2015/fallecio-jose-carrasco-tavara-ex-ministro-aprista |title=Falleci\u00f3 Jos\u00e9 Carrasco T\u00e1vara, ex ministro aprista |access-date=2015-01-19 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150119060122/http://www.larepublica.pe/16-01-2015/fallecio-jose-carrasco-tavara-ex-ministro-aprista |archive-date=2015-01-19 |url-status=dead }}</ref>\n\n== References ==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n{{commons category}}\n*[http://www.congreso.gob.pe/congresista/2006/jcarrasco/_hoja-vida.htm Official Congressional Site]\n\n{{Current Peruvian Congress}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Carrasco, Jose}}\n[[Category:2015 deaths]]\n[[Category:American Popular Revolutionary Alliance politicians]]\n[[Category:Members of the Congress of the Republic of Peru]]\n[[Category:1944 births]]\n\n\n{{Peru-politician-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{for|the Spanish footballer|Francisco Jos\u00e9 Carrasco}}\n{{for|the Colombian long-distance runner|Jos\u00e9 Alirio Carrasco}}\n[[File:Jos\u00e9 Carrasco 2.jpg|thumb|Jos\u00e9 Carrasco]]\n'''Jos\u00e9 Carlos Carrasco T\u00e1vara''' (1944 \u2013 18 January 2015) was a [[Peru]]vian politician and a [[Congress of Peru|Congressman]] representing [[Piura Region|Piura]] for the 2006-2011 term. Carrasco belonged to the [[Peruvian Aprista Party]]. He was born in Sullana.\n\nHe died in Lima on 18 January 2015 from lung cance